CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 20, 1962, pg. 1 reads:"President Kennedy Stumps Area for Democrats- In McKeesport, JFK is shown addressing thousands of people assembled in early morning."
TitMainTitle: John F. Kennedy speaking under awning to large crowd, with Hirshbergs, Peoples Union Bank, and Reubens in background, near intersection of Walnut Street and Lysle Boulevard, McKeesport
